title: This is the world's fastest growing economy, and it could grow an 'explosive' 100%
description: The world's fastest growing economy is on track for a more than 100% growth, largely fueled by profits from its oil production and export sector.

title: SoftBank-backed Improbable slashes losses by 85%, says pivot to the metaverse has paid off
description: Improbable, which is backed by SoftBank, said its revenues more than doubled last year after a pivot to powering new "metaverse" experiences.

title: Apple's Eddy Cue defends default search contract with Google as best option for consumers
description: Apple's head of services testified in federal court Tuesday about the company's agreement to make Google the default search engine on iPhones in the U.S.

title: Biden calls on Congress to fund government as Moody's and Wells Fargo warn of shutdown effects
description: President Joe Biden asked Congress to avoid a government shutdown due to lack of funds. The U.S. credit rating and dollar could be affected otherwise.

title: Miami man pleads guilty to selling adulterated, misbranded HIV drugs across U.S.
description: The misbranded HIV drugs, which included Truvada and Biktarvy, were distributed to pharmacies across the U.S. and dispensed to unsuspecting patients.

title: FTC and 17 states sue Amazon on antitrust charges
description: The lawsuit is a major milestone for FTC Chair Lina Khan, who rose to prominence for her 2017 Yale Law Journal note, "Amazon's Antitrust Paradox."

title: Grammy's CEO: 'We're not going to award AI creativity' unless it falls under these two categories
description: AI-generated music can go viral on social media, but it won't win a Grammy unless it falls into one of two categories, says Recording Academy CEO Harvey Mason Jr.

title: Fed's Neel Kashkari sees 40% chance of 'meaningfully higher' interest rates
description: Kashkari thinks there's nearly a 50-50 chance that interest rates will need to move significantly higher to bring down inflation.

title: JPMorgan's UK digital bank blocks customers from buying crypto
description: From Oct. 16, Chase UK customers will "no longer be able to make crypto transactions via debit card or by outgoing bank transfer."

title: Travelers say Tampa International is the best large airport in North America for the second year in a row
description: J.D. Power ranked large airports in North America based on customer satisfaction. Tampa International Airport took the top spot for the second year in a row.

title: JPMorgan Chase to settle Jeffrey Epstein sex trafficking suit by U.S. Virgin Islands for $75 million
description: Jeffrey Epstein was a long-time customer of JPMorgan Chase, the huge U.S. bank which previously agreed to pay his victims $290 million to settle a similar suit.

title: Saudi Arabia announces crucial step forward in its nascent nuclear power plans
description: The news comes amid increasing concern about Saudi Arabia's intentions with the technology, and the potential for a nuclear arms race in the Middle East.

title: Armenia warns of 'ethnic cleansing' as thousands flee the Nagorno-Karabakh enclave
description: The mass exodus comes after a lightening military operation by Azerbaijan last week saw it take full control of the region.

title: Hunter Biden sues former Trump lawyer Rudy Giuliani over infamous laptop
description: Hunter Biden has been the focus of attacks on his father, President Joe Biden, by Donald Trump, Rudy Giuliani, conservative members of Congress and media.

title: AI chip firm Kneron raises $49 million as it looks to rival Nvidia, with Foxconn among backers
description: Kneron is looking to capitalize on the investor interest in AI and the chip technology that underpins it, underscored by Nvidia's 180% rally this year.

title: Jamie Dimon says India optimism is 'completely justified'
description: JPMorgan Chase Chairman and CEO Jamie Dimon struck a bullish tone at the India Investor Summit.

title: Chinese e-commerce giant Alibaba plans to list its logistics unit Cainiao in Hong Kong
description: Alibaba plans to list its logistics unit Cainiao on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, the Chinese e-commerce giant said in a regulatory filing Tuesday.

title: Russia smells blood as Ukraine tries to stop war fatigue spreading among allies
description: Ukraine is trying to keep its international backers close as diplomatic gaffes, war fatigue and elections threaten to upset its alliances.

title: 'We have dealt with recessions before': Jamie Dimon says geopolitics is the world's biggest risk
description: JPMorgan Chase & Co. CEO Jamie Dimon says geopolitics in light of Russia's invasion in Ukraine is the biggest risk is a much larger risk than high inflation or a U.S. recession.

title: CNBC Daily Open: Has the BOJ been ambiguous in its communication?
description: Last Friday, the Japanese central bank maintained its ultra-loose policy and left rates unchanged, mindful of the "extremely high uncertainties" on the growth outlook.

title: EU trade chief says the outcome of China EV probe cannot be prejudged
description: Europe may have started investigating Chinese electric vehicle subsidies, but no assumptions should be made about the probe's outcome, the head of trade for the European bloc's executive branch said Tuesday.

title: Biden administration blacklists China firms for Moscow, Tehran drone links
description: The U.S. Department of Commerce added 28 entities to the U.S. Entity List on Monday, citing national security concerns.

title: Dads have a 'unique effect' on kids' attainment. Here's how
description: Kids whose dads read, sing and draw with them may have an advantage once they start school and get better grades, new research shows.

title: ‘Dark’ ships are faking their locations to move oil around the world — and it's likely worth billions of dollars
description: New technology has identified rising numbers of vessels that appear to be manipulating their location data to ship Russian oil — and evade the G7's price cap.

title: Fixing China's property sector could take years — if not a decade, says economist
description: China's urbanization drive may be drawing to a close — and that could further hurt the already ailing property sector, according to China economist Hao Hong.

title: I walked more than 100 miles in Kyoto. Here are 5 new places worth visiting
description: Artisanal shops are popping up across Kyoto — with matcha, coffee and guided meditation  —not far from the city's temples and famous sights.

title: Carousell says it's 'on track' to profitability, plans to reduce losses this year
description: Secondhand goods marketplace Carousell expects to "healthily" reduce its losses this year, putting it on track to profitability, the firm's CEO told CNBC.
